modules.description: The module provides operations for manipulating key-value mappings, including adding, removing, and querying entries, along with merging, filtering, and sequence-based transformations. It works with string-keyed maps, enabling tasks like configuration management and data processing through functional patterns such as folding and mapping. Use cases include efficiently handling dynamic data structures or converting between sequential and mapped representations.

Provides functions to parse JSON configuration files into OCaml records and serialize records back into JSON format. Works with OCaml's variant types, records, and standard library types like lists and strings. Used to load application settings from a file and save user preferences in a structured, type-safe manner.
